stimulusHtml: What is printed as a result of executing the code segment?

features.html:
Consider the following class definitions.

 

  • public class Item 
{ 
   private int IdNum; 
   
   public Item(int id) 
   { 
      IdNum = id; 
   }
   
   public int getIdNum() 
   {
      return IdNum; 
   }
   
   public void checkID(Checker c) 
   {
      c.validate(this); 
   }
}

     

  • public class Checker
{ 
   private int lastID = 0;
   
   public void validate(Item i) 
   { 
      int id = i.getIdNum();
      if (id == lastID) 
      {
         System.out.println("ID " + id + ": invalid"); 
      }
      else
      {
         lastID = id; 
         System.out.println("ID " + id + ": valid"); 
      }
   }
}

     

The following code segment appears in a class other than  Item  or  Checker.

 

Item i = new Item(23);
Item j = new Item(55);
Checker c = new Checker();

i.checkID(c);
j.checkID(c);
j.checkID(c);
i.checkID(c);
